DIV1.P:
A divine Sentence, says he, Verse 10. is in the Lips of the King; his Mouth transgresseth not in Judgment. The Hebrew is, Divination in the Lips, &c. That is, he speaks Oracles;
A great Sagacity and piercing Judgment to discern dubious and difficult Cases. Mr. Pool. in his Determinations in Judgment should be as tho' we had enqired of the Oracles of God, for the clear Disco∣very of the Truth, & the certain Direction in all weighty Matters, that there may be no Error or Mistake, in his Administrations; as one under the Influence and Inspira∣tion of God; with whom is the just Weight and Ballance, (as he adds in the next verse,) that is the Power to discern clearly, and determine justly. Such, in some good mea∣sure, was the admirable Foresight, and clear Discernment
of Solomon himsel, which his admiring Subjects with the deepest Veneration, rdred his Name famous in distant Lands, and brought the Queen of the South, from her far Country, to hear, and applaud his Wisdom.
